# Jongara UI Design Principles

Follow these design principles to create a unique, visually appealing interface that avoids being ordinary:

## 1. Unique Design Style
- Maintain brand consistency with the "Warm Wood, Carved Jade" color palette
- Use distinctive visual elements that reflect traditional East Asian aesthetics
- Design custom UI components rather than relying solely on standard Flutter widgets

## 2. Color Scheme Optimization
- Use the defined color harmony throughout the application
- Ensure sufficient contrast between text and backgrounds
- Apply colors purposefully to convey emotion and atmosphere

## 3. Typography
- Use clear, readable typography with proper hierarchy
- Maintain consistent font sizes and weights across the application
- No custom fonts required - use system fonts effectively

## 4. Visual Engagement
- Implement subtle animations for interactions (tile movements, selections)
- Add micro-interactions for button clicks and transitions
- Ensure animations enhance rather than distract from the experience

## 5. Attention to Detail
- Maintain proper spacing and alignment throughout the UI
- Provide clear visual feedback for all interactive elements
- Design intuitive icons and graphics that enhance clarity

## 6. Layout and Navigation
- Create intuitive, user-friendly navigation structures
- Ensure excellent display across various device sizes
- Implement responsive layouts that adapt to different screen orientations

## 7. User Experience
- Focus on simplicity, intuitiveness, and ease of use
- Ensure the game is accessible to players of all skill levels
- Provide clear visual cues for game mechanics

## 8. Visual Storytelling
- Use design elements to convey the zen-like, meditative nature of the game
- Create a cohesive visual experience that reinforces the game's theme
- Maintain a sense of tranquility and focus throughout the interface